name: presquile-national-wildlife-refuge-narrative-report-for-the-period-january-1-to-april-30-1-d5a04
notes: This narrative report for Presquile National Wildlife Refuge outlines Refuge accomplishments from January through April of 1956. The report begins by summarizing the weather conditions, water conditions, and food and cover during this period. Wildlife- including migratory birds, upland game birds, big game animals, predators, rodents, raptors, and fish- is also covered. The Refuge development and maintenance section discusses physical developments and plantings. A progress report on field investigations and applied research is also provided. The public relations section of the report describes recreational uses, Refuge visitors, and Refuge participation. Items of interest and N-R forms are attached.
